      <prefercite id="aspace_b46af279769aa05e1b0d1788f02963ca">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Anthony John Monk Collection on Paul Rudolph (MS 1928). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="aspace_fc9de01f628a46252296b3e9826169f9">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Anthony John Monk is an architect and educator, and a 1963 graduate of the Yale School of Architecture.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_559237bd0787af0c8bc7e2ff3290d965">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection consists of research notes and publicity materials for the book, <title type="simple" render="italic">
               The Art and Architecture of Paul Rudolph
            </title>, by Anthony John Monk. The collection also includes photographs and slides of several Rudolph buildings, as well as presentation boards for the Paisley Civic Center project in Scotland by the architectural firm Hutchinson Locke and Monk.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_8a3deddf2e711f490106089f8e456c79">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Arranged alphabetically by publication title and type of material.</p>  
      </arrangement>
